<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
Story 4-3 T6 — synthetic-consumer manifest (AC-2 positive case).

The <application> element intentionally declares NO android:allowBackup
attribute. The plugin's manifest declares android:allowBackup="false" with
tools:replace="android:allowBackup", so manifest-merger preserves the
plugin's value in the merged output. The merged manifest at
build/intermediates/merged_manifest/release/AndroidManifest.xml is greped by
.github/workflows/manifest_merge_audit.yml::audit-positive for the
allowBackup="false" + dataExtractionRules entry — AC-2 evidence.

DO NOT add android:allowBackup, android:dataExtractionRules, or
android:fullBackupContent here — that would invalidate the AC-2 inheritance
test (the warning-case sibling at ../synthetic-warning/ exercises the
opposite: consumer wins when the plugin has no tools:replace).
-->
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android">
    <application
        android:label="MwaSyntheticConsumer" />
</manifest>
